12:07.232 --> 12:08.853
Not in my lifetime, Frankie.

12:08.947 --> 12:10.983
It's not my thing.
None of it is my thing.

12:11.167 --> 12:13.445
I don't like attention.
I don't like giving speeches.

12:13.648 --> 12:15.101
Oh, okay.

12:15.200 --> 12:18.155
So that's what this is about--
the speech.

12:18.252 --> 12:20.402
I should have known.
No problem.

12:20.491 --> 12:22.071
I can help you.

12:22.404 --> 12:24.818
You-- you just have to say
a few words. That's all.

12:24.923 --> 12:28.105
You know, it's mostly just,
like, kind of thank people.

12:28.300 --> 12:30.672
I mean, you want to be
humble, but cool,

12:30.765 --> 12:32.180
also a little entertaining.

12:32.313 --> 12:36.581
Um, okay, so, what rhymes
with "limestone"?

12:36.676 --> 12:41.379
Uh, winebone, chimecone--
time zone!

12:41.593 --> 12:43.805
Yeah, no. Ohh, I don't know
what to do with that.

12:43.972 --> 12:44.794
Okay, you know what?

12:44.902 --> 12:46.925
Let's just--
let's just spitball here.

12:47.001 --> 12:48.811
Let's just
move some energy around.

12:48.907 --> 12:50.635
All right, I say a word,
you say a word.

12:50.720 --> 12:52.680
- I say "hard hat," you say...
- Good night.

12:52.789 --> 12:55.849
[ Sighs ] You know, you are
a really difficult person.

12:55.957 --> 12:58.037
Let's just say
you had to say something.

12:58.199 --> 13:00.840
Gun to your head,
you had to say something--

13:01.021 --> 13:02.196
what would it be?

13:02.358 --> 13:05.179
Uh, I guess I would say...

13:06.658 --> 13:10.093
"For 20 years, this job's put
a roof over my family's head.

13:10.457 --> 13:14.816
I've had a great group of guys
working for me--

13:14.921 --> 13:17.467
hard-working guys
who show up on time,

13:18.112 --> 13:19.945
rarely take sick days.

13:20.290 --> 13:22.160
We've seen
each other's kids grow up.

13:22.542 --> 13:25.788
I've been lucky,
not only for the work,

13:25.885 --> 13:30.472
but my crew has made this
a good place to go every day."

13:31.196 --> 13:33.126
Well, where have you been
hiding that?

13:33.224 --> 13:34.558
That's beautiful.

13:34.687 --> 13:36.429
Can't you just go and say that?

13:36.600 --> 13:37.957
It's one dinner, Mike.

13:38.054 --> 13:41.054
One dinner that maybe
doesn't mean a lot to you,

13:41.164 --> 13:44.539
but might mean a lot
to everyone else.

13:45.472 --> 13:47.616
- [ Groans ]
- Oh, yay!

13:47.715 --> 13:49.478
You're gonna be so good!

13:49.633 --> 13:51.570
You know, if I wasn't wearing
five pairs of pajamas,

13:51.656 --> 13:54.095
I would totally break out
the lady jazz.

13:54.233 --> 13:55.466
- Mm.
- Hmm.

13:56.609 --> 13:59.360
[ Bell rings ] I really had such
high hopes for Mix-It-Up Mondays.

13:59.465 --> 14:02.572
Eh, I guess there's always
gonna be an us and a them.

14:02.659 --> 14:03.699
I guess that's just
the way it is.

14:03.789 --> 14:06.265
Brad, you want to come to
the new brownie place with us?

14:06.393 --> 14:09.363
Deb says we have to hang
'cause you are hilarious!

14:09.464 --> 14:12.490
Wow! Make new friends,
but keep the old.

14:12.965 --> 14:14.125
See you tomorrow.

14:15.555 --> 14:16.685
Oh! I got to go, too.

14:16.806 --> 14:18.411
I sat by
the space mates yesterday,

14:18.520 --> 14:19.837
and they're not as nerdy
as we thought.

14:19.950 --> 14:21.261
We're gonna go
jump on the gym mats

14:21.398 --> 14:23.208
and act like
we're in zero gravity.

14:26.489 --> 14:27.452
Brian: Beep-beep!

14:27.797 --> 14:29.239
Molly, say hi to Ukraine.

14:30.243 --> 14:31.150
<i>And just when Sue thought</i>

14:31.249 --> 14:32.724
<i>things couldn't get</i>
<i>any worse...</i>

14:32.811 --> 14:34.409
- [ Sneezes ]
<i>- ...they did.</i>

14:34.516 --> 14:35.948
[ Coughs, snorts ]

14:36.570 --> 14:39.351
I think I got sick
from working so hard on JP-La...

14:39.450 --> 14:41.830
and waking up with frozen hair
didn't help.

14:41.960 --> 14:42.999
I just feel bad.

14:43.094 --> 14:45.156
I really want
to see dad win his award.

14:45.341 --> 14:47.194
Maybe we shouldn't
leave Sue here.

14:47.293 --> 14:48.810
Maybe we should
just all stay home.

14:48.931 --> 14:51.990
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
this is my big night, too.

14:52.111 --> 14:55.000
I've looked like Ernie and/or
Bert for the last 10 years.

14:55.078 --> 14:58.324
I finally look snazzy,
and I am showing it off.

14:58.670 --> 15:01.261
You're going,
and you're staying.

15:01.388 --> 15:03.739
Just drink lots of liquids.
Text me if you need anything.

15:03.825 --> 15:05.463
Don't run the toaster
if you're falling asleep.

15:05.556 --> 15:07.706
And if you're hungry, there's
popsicles on the counter.

15:07.811 --> 15:10.052
[ Sneezes ]
Good luck, dad.

15:10.148 --> 15:11.229
I hope you win.

15:11.569 --> 15:12.820
It's not a contest.

15:12.919 --> 15:14.032
I already won.

15:14.152 --> 15:16.074
Well, sometimes you think
you won,

15:16.168 --> 15:18.558
and then at the last minute,
you didn't.

15:18.665 --> 15:21.360
Wait for them
to call your name... twice.

15:21.446 --> 15:22.880
Twice. Got it.

15:24.513 --> 15:26.537
[ Laughter ]

15:27.329 --> 15:28.968
Bob: I know the real reason
you're giving me this--

15:29.061 --> 15:31.422
'cause I'm the guy who gives you
your paycheck every week.

15:31.508 --> 15:33.416
Am I right, Larry?

15:33.478 --> 15:35.623
Especially you.
You know what I'm talking about.

15:35.998 --> 15:38.447
Wow, who knew the accountant
was such a cut-up?

15:38.528 --> 15:39.983
Seriously, it's been
a joy to come to work.

15:40.075 --> 15:42.476
Nice suit, little dude.
Off the rack?

15:42.568 --> 15:45.209
- Out of the box.
- What's the label?

15:45.346 --> 15:46.687
I don't know.

15:47.221 --> 15:49.848
Shah-nee-a Twan.

15:50.649 --> 15:52.465
Shania Twain?

15:54.231 --> 15:56.987
"The, 'man, I feel
like a woman' collection."

15:57.213 --> 15:59.182
Oh, no,
this isn't Cousin Ryan's.

15:59.264 --> 16:00.776
It's Cousin Allison's.

16:00.904 --> 16:03.700
I've been wearing women's
clothes for the last three days.

16:03.888 --> 16:05.292
It's cool, baby Mike.

16:05.427 --> 16:08.686
Man, woman
we're all just energy.

16:09.057 --> 16:11.943
Okay, okay, I'm taking too much
of your time now.

16:12.351 --> 16:13.334
You got to save
some of that love

16:13.448 --> 16:16.284
for our other honoree--
Mike Heck.

16:16.436 --> 16:18.095
[ Applause ]

16:22.238 --> 16:24.227
Uh, yeah, oh, okay.

16:24.387 --> 16:25.396
[ Chuckles ]

16:25.930 --> 16:26.808
[ Clears throat ]

16:27.505 --> 16:28.947
I still don't get
why I'm up here.

16:29.121 --> 16:31.349
Uh, maybe I-I-I
just don't get it.

16:31.470 --> 16:34.993
But, you know, I had to lay off
four guys a couple months ago,

16:35.093 --> 16:38.147
and these were all guys
with families, you know?

16:38.244 --> 16:39.688
So it doesn't feel right
to be honoring me

16:39.770 --> 16:43.940
when I couldn't find a way
to save their jobs.

16:44.037 --> 16:44.949
And, you know,
I mean, am I--

16:45.080 --> 16:46.718
am I gonna
have to lay off 10 more?

16:47.334 --> 16:48.876
I don't know.
Look around the room.

16:48.952 --> 16:51.046
It's like, "Hey, is he next?
What about her?"

16:51.423 --> 16:52.476
But, hey, in this economy,

16:52.558 --> 16:54.943
we're all just hanging on
by a thread, right?

16:55.061 --> 16:57.106
I mean, look, everyone loves
Bob Branderson here,

16:57.184 --> 17:00.218
but they could, you know, hire
some outside accounting service,

17:00.330 --> 17:02.620
and then,
uh, he'd be out of a job.

17:03.515 --> 17:05.660
Hell,
the whole quarry could close.

17:05.779 --> 17:07.690
It's a threat
that we live with every day.

17:07.799 --> 17:11.512
So maybe longevity is something
that should be recognized?

17:11.578 --> 17:14.262
I don't know. Just saying,
uh, it seems weird to me.

17:14.349 --> 17:17.146
But, uh, it is what it is.

17:17.242 --> 17:19.815
So... yeah.

17:20.069 --> 17:21.758
I'll-- I'll--
I'll put this somewhere.

17:24.242 --> 17:26.031
[ Scattered applause ]

